title: $:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/readme
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! What it does

A keyboard-driven cascading command palette for TiddlyWiki. Hit one hotkey (default: ''Ctrl-Space'') to open. Type to filter a stage. ''→'' (Right-arrow) drills into a stage. ''Space'' opens the action menu on typed rows (works on containers too). ''Esc'' walks one stage back, ''Shift-Esc'' closes from any depth. ''Enter'' fires the selected action. Domain plugins (e.g. `rimir/orga-palette`) extend the palette by shipping declarative ''entry'' and ''action'' tiddlers — no widget code required.

! Key features

* ''Cascading stages'' — every drill pushes a new stage; ArrowLeft / Esc pops one stage at any depth, Shift-Esc closes from any depth. Breadcrumb shows where you are.
* ''Declarative protocol'' — adding a new cascade is one tiddler. Tag, fields, done.
* ''Generic engine'' — no domain knowledge baked in. Same widget serves any catalogue plugin.
* ''Multi-view root menu'' — switch between ''Entries'' / ''All tiddlers'' / ''By namespace'' / ''By parent'' / ''Hybrid'' views from a pill strip above the input. Each view is a composition of one or more ''structure layers'' (`ca-view-layers` lists them) — each layer declaring its own `roots` + `children` filters, row decorations, and optional `row-entity-type` for context-action drilling. A focusable ''Structure'' strip below the view pills makes the active view's composition externally visible: compact by default (one summary row with view name + layer-count + view-scoped pills), expandable on Enter/Space/→ to a full stacked layout (view-scoped header + one mini-row per layer with all primitive pills). Arrow keys navigate the expanded grid; each focused pill renders contextual help into the details drawer. Entries can opt into per-view placement via `ca-position-<view-slug>` fields. Add your own views as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/view` and your own layers as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/structure-layer`.
* ''Leader keys'' — type a single char and idle for 200ms to fire a shortcut: `x` clears all filter+visibility pills, `>` opens a tree-picker that commits a path as a title-prefix filter, `s` saves the current state as a named preset, `r` jumps focus to the preset strip. Every visible leader is also surfaced as a pill in the ''Leader'' strip above the input, so the available gestures are discoverable without prior knowledge — Tab into the strip, ←/→ to select, ↵/Space to fire. Leaders may be view-scoped via ''`ca-leader-views`'' (a filter producing view titles) — empty / missing means global. Author your own as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader`.
* ''Presets'' — save any combination of active view + filter pills + visibility pills under a name; replay later by picking the preset's pill. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/preset`.
* ''Filter strip'' — type `/foo`, `prefix:work/`, `#tag`, `@<tiddler>` to stack ''filter'' pills that narrow every result list. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/filter`.
* ''Visibility strip'' — type `hide:appify` to hide entries by group, or Shift-DEL on a root row to hide a single entry. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility`. Ctrl-DEL clears both filter and visibility strips.
* ''Filter substitution'' — `<<query>>`, `<<picked>>`, `<<parent-picked>>`, `<<context-tiddler>>` available in every filter and action. Filter/visibility expressions also see `<arg>` and `<<arg>>`.
* ''Keyboard-first'' — Up/Down to select, Tab to cycle sections (input → preset → visibility → filter → view → structure → leader → menu → details), Esc to walk one stage back (closes only at root from input), Shift-Esc to close from any depth, Enter to fire. ''→'' drills into containers / opens actions on typed leaves; ''Space'' opens actions on any typed row including containers. Left/Right inside the input preserve normal cursor behaviour.

! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki ≥ 5.4.0

! Quick start

Install the plugin, restart. Ctrl-Space opens the palette. Out of the box you get four demo entries (Open Control Panel, Save Wiki, Advanced Search, Recent Tiddlers…) so you can confirm it's working. The real value is in shipping your own ''entry'' and ''action'' tiddlers — see the [[Documentation]] tab for the protocol.

To rebind, edit the tiddler `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open`.

! Extending: the action-tiddler protocol

* ''Entry tiddlers'' — root-stage menu items. Tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`.
* ''Action tiddlers'' — what appears in the action menu for a picked entity. Tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action`, scoped via `ca-entity-type` field.

Each tiddler declares whether it's a ''leaf'' (fires actions on Enter and closes) or a ''drill'' (pushes a new stage). Cascades form an implicit graph: a drill from type A → type B is just a tiddler with `ca-entity-type: A` and `ca-next-entity-type: B`. Add a new edge by writing one tiddler.

See the Documentation tab's ''Protocol'' section for full schema and worked examples.
